# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Binary media assets: ignored by default.
#
# This is an image-compression skill, so any image/video file in the tree is a
# test fixture, not source code. Treating them as untracked keeps the repo
# small, prevents accidentally publishing private assets, and avoids confusion
# about what's "real" code vs. what's a test sample.
#
# *** SVG is included on purpose ***
# Normally SVG is source code (logos, icons in components). But in THIS repo
# SVG files are also compression test fixtures — same role as JPG/PNG. So we
# ignore SVG too.
#
# If you ever want to commit a specific image (e.g. a screenshot for docs):
#   git add -f path/to/file.png
# Or add a `!` exception below for a whole directory.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif
*.webp
*.avif
*.heic
*.heif
*.bmp
*.tif
*.tiff
*.svg
*.mp4
*.mov
*.webm
*.psd
*.ai

# Local per-project test configs (not for sharing)
imgopt.config.mjs
imgopt.config.js
imgopt.config.json
